---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Willy W. | AI-Native Builder"
  description="I build real systems with AI as a one-person engineering team."
>
  <div class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
    <p class="kicker">whoami</p>
    <h1 id="hero-title">
      I build real systems with AI &mdash; <em>as a one-person engineering team.</em>
    </h1>
    <p>
      Trading bots, research pipelines, and automation &mdash; designed, built, and shipped by
      orchestrating Claude, Codex, and Obsidian. Not a traditional developer; proof of what one
      motivated person can ship with today's AI tools.
    </p>
    <div class="cta">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/projects">See my projects</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/about">How I work with AI &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section aria-labelledby="projects-title">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <h2 id="projects-title">Active projects</h2>
      <a href="/projects">all &rarr;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="cards">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="chip active">ACTIVE</span>
        <h3>Spot Grid Trading Bot</h3>
        <p>
          A Python grid-trading bot with a safety-first design: testnet-first rollout,
          sign-only wallet permissions, and a standalone risk engine.
        </p>
        <div class="stack">python &middot; exchange-api &middot; risk-engine</div>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="chip active">ACTIVE</span>
        <h3>Agentic Knowledge Pipeline</h3>
        <p>
          A daily automated pipeline where multiple AI agents ingest, process, and file
          research into a structured Obsidian vault.
        </p>
        <div class="stack">multi-agent &middot; obsidian &middot; scheduling</div>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="chip shelved">SHELVED &middot; BY DATA</span>
        <h3>Prediction-Market Backtester</h3>
        <p>
          Built a weather-market strategy tester, ran a pre-registered experiment on ~170
          paper trades &mdash; and killed the strategy when the data said no.
        </p>
        <div class="stack">python &middot; statistics &middot; honesty</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="writing-title">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <h2 id="writing-title">Writing</h2>
      <a href="/blog">all posts &rarr;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="posts">
      <div class="post">
        <a href="/blog">How I run a two-AI dev team: Codex builds, Claude reviews</a>
        <time datetime="2026-07">2026-07</time>
      </div>
      <div class="post">
        <a href="/blog">Killing my own strategy: what a negative result taught me</a>
        <time datetime="2026-06">2026-06</time>
      </div>
      <div class="post">
        <a href="/blog">My Obsidian + Claude knowledge pipeline, end to end</a>
        <time datetime="2026-06">2026-06</time>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="toolkit-title">
    <div class="toolkit">
      <div>
        <h3 id="toolkit-title">The AI Toolkit</h3>
        <p>
          The exact stack and division of labor I use &mdash; and why it minimizes
          hallucination while maximizing shipping speed.
        </p>
        <div class="pipe">
          claude <span>(architect/review)</span> &rarr; codex <span>(build)</span> &rarr;
          obsidian <span>(memory)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/toolkit">Explore &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
